<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Rockman X2 with DIP36toTSOP40 mkiii and wires...]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=16533&amp;p=205849#p205849"><![CDATA[
Sweet lord I finally got it... (About 500 points of soldering later...) Rockman X2 with my patch is now running beautifully. Wired up /ce from chip to gnd on board. send /ce from board to a20 and then tie a21, vcc, and a22 to gnd. did not add mirroring. voila. <br /><br />Update: Mirrored last 512kb to make rom 2mb then merged with rockman x3 and added a switch. Just took gnd off a22 and connected to vcc to run x3 on lower half of chip. Kept the switch inside until i can get a reset counter chip...<br /><br /> oh btw on another note i also found a &quot;new project zero 3&quot; rom that works on copiers. Its 4mb so i cant use it with this project but i would like people to know about it as i thought project zero didnt run on copiers! One noticeable difference is that it does not say 2015 or whatever at the beginning...<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5795">rocklite</a> — Thu Oct 12, 2017 12:13 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
