<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=16533&amp;p=205257#p205257"><![CDATA[
Cannot for life of me seem to get X2 board to work with 29f033c chips with wires and those buyicnow boards. My goal is to have X2 with a &quot;start with armor&quot; game genie patch and i think im very close. I have almost exhausted myself researching this as most of the info i can find people are trying to put together a megaman x2 and x3 board using retrostage super fx converters. I am presuming these boards are just a cleaner and easier option as they all seem to have the same address(?). <br /><br />I have attempted to get this going by populating both slots on the board with a 27c801 and a 27c101 (1mb + 512kb) and two 27c801 (1mb + 1mb [mirrored?]) and a 29f033c chip as well with some results...<br /><br />I normally play this patched rom via the superufo pro 8 with my Rockman X2 in the top and every &quot;experiment&quot; ive tried gives me different results. I like to use the superufo's &quot;play cart&quot; option for all my repros as it gives the message &quot;no cartridge&quot; when my soldering is bad. <br /><br />With the 27c801 it seems to boot but the graphics freeze as a garbled mess of sprites replacing x riding the bike appears and promptly locks up. <br /><br />I finally got the 29f033c to read as a cart through the super ufo but it locks up DIRECTLY as the capcom logo dissapears. I read that byuu said to patch the rom by changing address #$01 to #$00 but ive no idea how to do that. <br /><br />The messed up sprites could also be board damage i suppose. Anyone else have any luck with this board? Ideally I would die to have it be x2 &amp; X3 but i have no clue what an &quot;and&quot; gate is or how to wire it up...<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5795">rocklite</a> — Tue Sep 26, 2017 12:23 pm</p><hr />
